(217, 1, '2014-07-27 15:39:38', '2014-07-27 15:39:38', '<h2 dir="ltr"><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/55108392?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;color=2ea3d1" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></h2>\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Church Concert Hall</h2>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Church Concert Hall is the original sanctuary space of Saint Brigid’s church. As the building is protected by heritage, all the original artwork and décor of the church remain, including the pews. Over the last few years, this space has been used for weddings ceremonies, private receptions, charity fundraisers, and corporate parties, as well as a variety of musical concerts and theatrical performances.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capacity: 699 (original church pews remain)</li>\r\n	<li>Located on the upper-level of Saint Brigid’s – Entrance is on St. Patrick Street.</li>\r\n	<li>Approximately 4500 square feet</li>\r\n	<li>Smart Stage installed at altar (Approximately 1400 square feet)</li>\r\n	<li>Stage Lighting: 36 spots with lighting board, plus house lights</li>\r\n	<li>Basic 4-channel P/A system available</li>\r\n	<li>Washrooms are located in the reception space in the basement – this space is not accessible by wheelchair.</li>\r\n	<li>Tables, chairs, podium available.</li>\r\n	<li>Bar services available</li>\r\n	<li>Wheelchair accessible by side door ramp entrance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a style="color: #1a7ebe;" href="http://saintbrigidscentre.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Church-Concert-Hall-Floor-Plan-dimensioned.pdf" target="_blank">View Church Concert Hall Plan [pdf]</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">The Kildare Room</h2>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Kildare Room is located in the basement space of Saint Brigid’s Centre. This room features newly repointed original stone walls, beautifully renovated washrooms, gallery lighting and most importantly, versatility. This space is exceptionally adaptable to different events and ideal for wedding receptions, banquets, private parties, small concerts and performances, and art exhibitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capacity: 258 standing, 200 theatrical seating, 170 banquet seating</li>\r\n	<li>Located in the basement of Saint Brigid’s – entrance is located on Cumberland Street.</li>\r\n	<li>Approximately 50’ x 50’</li>\r\n	<li>16’ x16’ stage</li>\r\n	<li>Stage lighting: 8 spotlights in front, 8 LEDs at the back, with lighting board, plus house lights</li>\r\n	<li>Gallery lighting along side walls</li>\r\n	<li>Projector screen installed on stage</li>\r\n	<li>Basic 4-channel P/A system available</li>\r\n	<li>5 individual unisex washroom units</li>\r\n	<li>Tables, chairs, podium available.</li>\r\n	<li>Bar services available</li>\r\n	<li>This space is not accessible by wheelchair</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a style="color: #1a7ebe;" href="http://saintbrigidscentre.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Kildare-Room-Floor-Plan-dimensioned.pdf" target="_blank">View Kildare Room Floor Plan [pdf]</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Book Your Event With Saint Brigid''s Today', 'Book your event at Saint Brigid''s Centre for the Arts today!', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'book-your-event-with-saint-brigids-today', '', '', '2014-07-27 15:55:00', '2014-07-27 15:55:00', '', 0, 'http://saintbrigidscentre.com/?post_type=event&#038;p=217', 0, 'event', '', 0),
